      "name": "Future Sustainability",
      "settings": {
        "section_id": "future_sustainbility",
        "heading": "Looking ahead: biodiversity and regeneration",
        "textfirst": "<p>As caretakers of this land for more than 175 years, we feel a deep responsibility to protect and enhance its natural character for future generations. In recent years, we’ve completed large-scale native tree planting across the gullies and hills surrounding our Taradale home – an initiative aimed at restoring habitats and naturally reducing our carbon footprint.</p>\n\n<p>Our estate supports a rich ecosystem, with abundant birdlife, wetlands, woodlands, and a working sheep and cattle farm. The Taipo Stream runs through our home vineyards and is monitored by the Hawke’s Bay Regional Council – a reflection of our ongoing commitment to the health of this land and its waterways.</p>\n\n<h4>Sustainability resources</h4>",
        "button_1_url": "",
        "button_1_text": "",
        "button_2_url": "",
        "button_2_text": "",
        "button_3_url": "",
        "button_3_text": "",
        "button_4_url": "",
        "button_4_text": "",
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Asset_1222.png",
        "slideshow_image_1": "shopify://shop_images/Asset_1_79d1ef41-95da-4075-ac16-dd6d5b2798e4.png",
        "padding_top_desktop": 50,
